      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsTitle" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><br>
            New Staff Found!&nbsp;&nbsp; <span class="NewsUser">Thalador 
            - 13-02-2001 at 11:46:01</span> 
            <br>
		  <span class="NewsTitleDescription">This is just a practical joke.</span>
		  </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			Our very own Wizard, Chasryan, seems to have come across a page on EverCrest that allows you to creat an item and it generates the little "Item Description" window that pops up when you right-click an item.<br><br>So it would seem that any of you who saw this and thought it was real, including Aegis and MYSELF have just fallen prey to an early April Fool's Day joke.<br><br>I STILL don't know what else to say to this, I'm STILL speachless!<br><br>Thalador<br>Wizard Class Leader<br>
          </td>
