      <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
        <tr bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
          <td width="32" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          <td class="NewsText" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
            <br>
			Our Temporary Initiation stop is no longer in effect.<br><br>Not that we have gotten all the Clerics, Enchanters and Monks we need, far from it, but simply on the basis of the Council recieving a lot of Applications from people who have possible ties with potential applicants of precisely these classes.<br><br>Its only fair that we allow all classes equal access, so friends and allies can join on equal terms.<br><br>Also we have experienced a large rate of high-levels leaving Aegis to either pursue different goals or because we have the max. 2 Character rule.<br><br>So, we open up the doors, confident that with our new High and Medium Level Event Masters, our Allies and the general rise in member-dedication, we will be able to address the needs of all new and existing members for a challenging and fun Aegis Lux.<br><br>But, remember, if ye see a sad Cleric, Chanter or Monkie, drop him a tell and ask him if he or she has ever heard of the illustrious Aegis Lux...You never know ;-)<br><br>- Errol
          </td>
          <td width="16" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
